Software and developer documentation

Project overview 
The PowerFlex API provides unified, secure, and consistent access to manage storage infrastructure through automation, enabling integration with DevOps tools and workflows.

Audience
The audience for the PowerFlex API is developers and customers who are using the PowerFlex Block REST API to deploy block storage on PowerFlex nodes and the PowerFlex Manager REST API to manage and orchestrate their PowerFlex Nodes.

Objective
The objecive was to colloborate with Engineering and User Experience Design to create APi documnetation that reflected the new PowerFlex deployment method. The documentaton needed to provide reference information that enables the user to deploy 
PowerFlex nodes using the APIs.

Your role
My role was as lead API documentation writer on the project. 

Deliverable
The deliverables were the following:
* API reference documentation: [PowerFlex Manager Bootstrapper API 4.8.0] (https://developer.dell.com/apis/4008/versions/4.5.5-Manager_v4-8-0/modules/7224)
* API conceptual documentation: [Getting started deploying PowerFlex nodes] (https://developer.dell.com/apis/4008/versions/4.5.5-Manager_v4-8-0/getting-started-with-deploying-powerflex-nodes-10344m0
